                            <comment id="13529531" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 01:09:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So far this is only a known issue for 4.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13529561" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 01:46:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In 5.x I am already using core.getNewIndexDir() when getting the file list for replication - I must have changed to that doing the Directory based replication work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4.x is still using core.getIndexDir().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13529563" author="commit-tag-bot" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 01:52:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;trunk commit&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Mark Robert Miller&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=1420507&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=1420507&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4168&quot; title=&quot;In recovery, replication occurs but all files are 0 in length and trying to open an indexwriter on the index fails, causing a loop with this issue.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4168&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-4168&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: 5x changes entry&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13529568" author="commit-tag-bot" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 02:00:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;branch_4x commit&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Mark Robert Miller&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=1420509&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=1420509&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4168&quot; title=&quot;In recovery, replication occurs but all files are 0 in length and trying to open an indexwriter on the index fails, causing a loop with this issue.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4168&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-4168&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Ensure we are using the absolute latest index dir when getting list of files for replication.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13529573" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 02:07:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That should solve a couple of the recent 4x test failures.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13530063" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 16:10:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So something is still happening here - doesn&apos;t seem that was the issue or only issue. Still not a problem seen on 5.x though. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13530644" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 13 Dec 2012 03:40:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was causing most of the fails waiting on recovery in 4.x tests. I still don&apos;t know why it was happening, but it has not shown up with the now back ported 5x replication code that uses a Directory.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
